[{"id":"1","title":"Hedersg\u00e4stintervju: Lena Karlin","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Interview"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"20:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0007","name":"Mats Dannewitz Linder (moderator)"},{"id":"0005","name":"Lena Karlin"}],"desc":"<p>Hedersg&auml;sten Lena Karlin intervjuas av Mats Linder.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"2","title":"Hedersg\u00e4stintervju: \u00c5sa Schwarz","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Interview"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"15:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0006","name":"Bellis (moderator)"},{"id":"0008","name":"\u00c5sa Schwarz"}],"desc":"<p>Hedersg&auml;sten &Aring;sa Schwarz intervjuas av Bellis<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"3","title":"Autonomous cars","tags":["Track:Science","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"12:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0008","name":"\u00c5sa Schwarz"},{"id":"A0020","name":"Ann Olsson Rousset"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-44ce562c-7fff-6ed3-aaa2-5411592bc8f0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Ann and &Aring;sa talk on modern and cars in the future. Development, obstacles, even hacker attacks. Why can this be difficult? Technical, surroudings, law and humans. <\/span><\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"5","title":"Fictional Animals - Discussion group","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"14:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0088","name":"Moa R\u00e5hlander (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Exobiology is a current feature in the literature. You may note the Gaia-worlds as in Avatar, the large extra terrestrial animals in Julie E Czerneda's books or the spiders in the books by Adrian Tchaikovsky. We discuss the animals in books, films and comics. Mention your favorites, the best, the worst and the most corny. Perhaps the discussion can frame when an author would use a fictional animal, and why.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Another interesrting topic to discuss is when an extra terrestrial would be understood as an animal and when they would be an intelligent being.<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"6","title":"Drinking tea","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"16:00","mins":"45","loc":["Kafeet"],"people":[{"id":"A0096","name":"Anna Gomez Lagerl\u00f6f (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-be6f8201-7fff-345c-6d86-6bad399ad649\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">I fantastiken dricks det mycket te. Te diskuteras som st&auml;mningsmark&ouml;r, kulturb&auml;rare och v&auml;g till visdom. Vi samlas i kaf&eacute;et, dricker te och pratar.<\/span><\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"7","title":"Marc Caro och Jean-Pierre Jeunet: film","tags":["Track:Film","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"20:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0020","name":"Ann Olsson Rousset (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-39225983-7fff-e488-88b7-5ad5dc3a7a8a\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Har du sett Delikatessen eller Barnens f&ouml;rlorade stad? St&auml;mningen och v&auml;rldarna &auml;r roliga, konstiga och alldeles underbara. Vi pratar ocks&aring; om \"Alien &aring;teruppst&aring;r\" och \"Am&eacute;lie fr&aring;n Montmartre\". Caro och Jeunet har tillsammans och var f&ouml;r sig skapat n&aring;gra av de mest speciella och roliga filmer som setts. Vi ser p&aring; filmklipp, bilder och pratar om ber&auml;ttarstil.<\/span><\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"8","title":"Excavating ancient and extraterrestrial civilizations","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"14:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0088","name":"Moa R\u00e5hlander (moderator)"},{"id":"0017","name":"Ian Sales"},{"id":"A0024","name":"Martin Rundkvist"},{"id":"A0028","name":"Jonathan Olsson"},{"id":"A0193","name":"Barbara Jane"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Other planets have a long history too, and the process of excavation is a literal means for protagonists to uncover the depth of those histories. <\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">This panel explores Mars, Rama, Murderbot and many others. Why are ancient civilizations so attractive? Are ancient civilizations on other planets so different from those on our own planet, when we excavate them?<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">This panel will talk about xenoarcheology in litterature and in possible future reality.<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"9","title":"Open craft caf\u00e9","tags":["Track:Maker","Division:Programming","Type:Workshop"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"14:00","mins":"45","loc":["Annat - -"],"people":[{"id":"A0055","name":"Sidsel Horvei (moderator)"},{"id":"A0020","name":"Ann Olsson Rousset"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-824aa526-7fff-5db1-141b-baca0cd60da1\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Bring your stuff: knitting, embroidery, spinning, sewing or what it may be. We sit and work and talk. Show and tell or just be at ease for a while with your creation.<\/span><\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"10","title":"What is Space Opera?","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"17:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0121","name":"Karl-Johan Nor\u00e9n (moderator)"},{"id":"A0061","name":"Sam Aalto"},{"id":"A0151","name":"H\u00e5kan Wester"},{"id":"A0154","name":"Larissa Ekonoja"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\"><span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"text-wrap: nowrap;\">What is really Space Opera? Empires, war, megalomania can often be ingredients, but opinions differs.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\"><span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"text-wrap: nowrap;\">The panel participants analyses and explains how they understand the term and what they would quote as examples.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\"><span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"text-wrap: nowrap;\">There will be different opinions among the participants: What can be labelled Space Opera?<\/span><\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"11","title":"Prepare for Impact- Rewatching Star Trek part II ","tags":["Track:Media","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"19:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0008","name":"Carolina G\u00f3mez Lagerl\u00f6f (moderator)"},{"id":"A0019","name":"Saga Bolund"},{"id":"A0025","name":"Marika L\u00f6vstr\u00f6m"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Star Trek panel from Konflikt cannot get enough of Star Trek. The discussion and analysis of old Star Trek episodes continues.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-2ebd7064-7fff-a3f7-287b-684bafdf156b\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"12","title":"Fantastic worlds we would like to visit","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"18:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0094","name":"Kristina H\u00e5rd (moderator)"},{"id":"A0061","name":"Sam Aalto"},{"id":"A0088","name":"Moa R\u00e5hlander"},{"id":"A0115","name":"Thomas Olivieri"},{"id":"A0146","name":"Anders Blixt"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Science fiction and fantasy depict many different worlds and societies. Which are the most appealing? The places, times and worlds we would like to live in or to visit? But could one persons dream be another's nightmare?<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-9772a4d9-7fff-ca0f-951f-b5f1f1efbaf2\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"13","title":"Fantastic worlds we would hate to visit","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"20:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0003","name":"Britt-Louise Viklund (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Science fiction and fantasy depict many different worlds and societies. Which are the nightmares? The places, times and worlds that are interesting and exciting to read about\/watch but a nightmare to live in?&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d3b69e3-7fff-7283-f020-cb7cec5d5c41\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"15","title":"Fiction prescription","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"11:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0019","name":"Saga Bolund (moderator)"},{"id":"0011","name":"Anna Davour"},{"id":"0017","name":"Ian Sales"},{"id":"0020","name":"Jenny Bristle"},{"id":"A0097","name":"Johan Anglemark"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f43ca21d-7fff-815f-f8d8-45313b1d2ef7\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Do you like space opera or sociological sf? Is Tolkien, grimdark or hopepunk your cup of tea? Our well read panelists will help you match wishes and interests with the right book. Come and tell the panel about your favorites and they will recommend something that could be a new reading experience, or perhaps a new favorite author. No request is too specific!<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"16","title":" The Multiverse - creative asset or disadvantage?","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"13:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0057","name":"Stefan H\u00f6gberg (moderator)"},{"id":"0011","name":"Anna Davour"},{"id":"A0004","name":"Johan J\u00f6nsson"},{"id":"A0106","name":"Boel Bermann"},{"id":"A0133","name":"Gunilla Jonsson"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-98332b34-7fff-2427-d200-288d8de6e702\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Variations of what is called the multiverse have appeared a lot in fantastic stories lately, both in literature and on film\/tv. Sure, it can be the basis of an exciting story. But how exciting is it really when every potential world or event is possible? How touching is the heroic death of a character if the same character always may return somewhere in the multiverse? What are the examples of good or poor use of this concept?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"17","title":"Housekeeping in space: Who\u00b4s cleaning the space ship?","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"19:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0024","name":"Gwen Frazer (moderator)"},{"id":"0010","name":"Torill Kornfeldt"},{"id":"A0083","name":"Vesa Sis\u00e4tt\u00f6"},{"id":"A0138","name":"Saara Henriksson"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-467f58ab-7fff-c8d2-d9f4-5b6c7acb3f8b\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Adventures among the planets is fun to read about and watch. But who takes care of the practicalities? Who does the cleaning and prepares the food? By what method is the trash sorted and taken care of and is there no need to wash your clothes in space? In books and movies little time is spent on these questions. What are the examples of interesting solutions? Robots or nanoparticles? Living space ships that absorb the dirt? Or would the brave space farers perhaps bring mum along to take care of the dishes?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"19","title":"Wandering the world's conventions","tags":["Track:Fan Interest","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"13:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0008","name":"Carolina G\u00f3mez Lagerl\u00f6f (moderator)"},{"id":"0021","name":"Thomas Recktenwald"},{"id":"0024","name":"Gwen Frazer"},{"id":"A0011","name":"Jukka Halme"},{"id":"A0035","name":"Luke Smith"},{"id":"A0103","name":"Bridget Wilkinson"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c6f1826b-7fff-25a7-bd90-b7007276ea87\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">The world is full of exciting science fiction and fantasy conventions. But how does one find them, join them, prepare for them, and what should one bring along for them? And why should we attend a convention far away in a country where we do not even know the language? Experienced convention travelers draw on their breadth of experience in attending conventions&nbsp; held in another language, how to select the conventions to go to and&nbsp; how to choose the right luggage for a long, convention-oriented trip.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"20","title":"Sp\u00f6khistoria i stearinljusets sken. ","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Reading"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"21:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"0003","name":"Nina Grensj\u00f6"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Sp&ouml;khistoria i stearinljusets sken.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3483c471-7fff-6855-7575-b6a574762ae5\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"21","title":"Economics of Extraterrestrial Mining","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"19:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0010","name":"Jesper Stage"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #215e99; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 14.6667px; background-color: #ffffff;\">When we settle other worlds, it will be cheaper to mine some of the materials we need on those worlds rather than bring them from Earth. But will mines on other worlds ever be a reason to establish settlements in the first place? Mining colonies are a popular staple of SF, but how plausible are they? In this talk we will look at what some of the economics of extraterrestrial mining might look like in reality, and compare with how we see this treated in SF.<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"22","title":"How did the Norse use skulls during the Viking Period?","tags":["Track:Science","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"21:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0024","name":"Martin Rundkvist (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: 'times new roman', serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">From the period AD 750-1050 there are a number of finds of human skulls in rather odd contexts around the Nordic region. Archaeologist Martin Rundkvist reports on new research into this overlooked find category. How were skulls used during the Viking Period?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"23","title":"To write in different genres","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"18:15","mins":"30","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0041","name":"Patrik Centerwall (moderator)"},{"id":"0005","name":"Lena Karlin"},{"id":"0008","name":"\u00c5sa Schwarz"},{"id":"0027","name":"T. L. Huchu"},{"id":"A0110","name":"Juliet McKenna"}],"desc":"<p>What are the challenges with writing in multiple different genres? How do different genres' requirements affect approaches to writing, research, and even writing environment (such as playlists, for authors who use them)?&nbsp; Is the same planning and research needed when writing science fiction, fantasy, detective stories, romance or literary fiction? How do writing style and character portrayals vary depending on the genre?<\/p>\r\n<p>Complicating genre-switching, how do those differences collide or cooperate when fusing them into multi-genre words? The panel explores how they have approached these challenges in their own word.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"24","title":"Lunchm\u00f6te: Min f\u00f6rsta kongress","tags":["Track:Trackless events","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"11:00","mins":"45","loc":["Ute"],"people":[{"id":"A0097","name":"Johan Anglemark (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p>&Auml;r Fantastika din f&ouml;rsta kongress? Vill du ha s&auml;llskap p&aring; lunchen? F&ouml;lj med p&aring; lunch tillsammans med n&aring;gra erfarna kongressbes&ouml;kare f&ouml;r att f&aring; reda p&aring; mer om kongresser och fandom. Vi g&aring;r till ett lunchst&auml;lle i n&auml;rheten.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"25","title":"Lunchm\u00f6te: Mina favoriter","tags":["Track:Trackless events","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"12:00","mins":"45","loc":["Ute"],"people":[{"id":"A0096","name":"Anna Gomez Lagerl\u00f6f (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p>Vill du f&ouml;lja med p&aring; lunch? Vi kommer att prata om&nbsp; v&aring;ra favoritb&ouml;cker och tv-serier. Vi g&aring;r till ett lunchst&auml;lle i n&auml;rheten.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"26","title":"Opening ceremony","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Other"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"18:00","mins":"15","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0005","name":"Lena Karlin"},{"id":"0008","name":"\u00c5sa Schwarz"},{"id":"0027","name":"T. L. Huchu"},{"id":"A0110","name":"Juliet McKenna"}],"desc":"<p>V&auml;lkommen till Fantastika!<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"27","title":"Closing ceremony","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Participatory Event"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"16:30","mins":"30","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0005","name":"Lena Karlin"},{"id":"0008","name":"\u00c5sa Schwarz"},{"id":"0027","name":"T. L. Huchu"},{"id":"A0008","name":"Carolina G\u00f3mez Lagerl\u00f6f"},{"id":"A0110","name":"Juliet McKenna"}],"desc":"<p>Tack f&ouml;r denna g&aring;ng!<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"28","title":"Sweconomr\u00f6stning och utdelning av Alvarpriset","tags":["Track:Fan Interest","Division:Programming","Type:Meeting"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"17:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0001","name":"Tomas Cronholm"},{"id":"A0008","name":"Carolina G\u00f3mez Lagerl\u00f6f"}],"desc":"<p>Var kommer n&auml;sta &aring;r Swecon att vara? Var med och r&ouml;sta! &Aring;rets Alvarpris delas ut.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"30","title":"Maria Gripes olika ansikten","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"15:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0006","name":"Bellis (moderator)"},{"id":"0003","name":"Nina Grensj\u00f6"},{"id":"0030","name":"Elin Holmerin"},{"id":"A0136","name":"Ylva Sp\u00e5ngberg"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">M&aring;nga av oss har vuxit upp med Maria Gripes b&ouml;cker som ofta klassificeras som magisk realism. Vilka b&ouml;cker och personer minns vi och vad var det som f&aring;ngade oss i l&auml;sningen?&nbsp; Maria Gripe var f&ouml;re sin tid i sina skildringar av manligt-kvinnligt genom karakt&auml;rer som Berta och framf&ouml;rallt Caroline i Skuggserien. Har det bidragit till b&ouml;ckernas popularitet och tidl&ouml;shet och att de bearbetats till teaterpj&auml;s och tv-serie?<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-8c18b175-7fff-fe33-c88e-25b0777894c5\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"31","title":" Guest of Honour interview: Juliet McKenna","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Interview"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"17:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0097","name":"Johan Anglemark (moderator)"},{"id":"A0110","name":"Juliet McKenna"}],"desc":"<p>Guest of Honour Juliet McKenna will talk to Johan Anglemark.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"32","title":" Guest of Honour interview: T L Huchu","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Interview"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"13:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0033","name":"Marianna \"Kisu\" Leikomaa (moderator)"},{"id":"0027","name":"T. L. Huchu"}],"desc":"<p>Guest of Honour T L Huchu will talk to Marianna Leikomaa<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"33","title":"Kulla Gulla - en svensk sagoprinsessa","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"18:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0003","name":"Britt-Louise Viklund (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-95fe6205-7fff-e021-7778-8f2d95ad3fb7\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Det finns ett tydligt klassperspektiv i Kulla Gulla men b&ouml;ckerna inneh&aring;ller ocks&aring; n&auml;rmast fantastiska element som en \"trollgubbe\" med helande f&ouml;rm&aring;ga och onda motst&aring;ndare. Gulla v&auml;xer upp p&aring; det fattiga Kullatorpet och f&aring;r arbeta h&aring;rt. Sedan hamnar hon, likt en \"choosen one\" av det r&auml;tta blodet, p&aring; herrg&aring;rden och f&aring;r till slut sin dr&ouml;mprins. Flickan med det&nbsp; blonda h&aring;ret har egenskaper som en hj&auml;lte med sitt mod och sin frispr&aring;kighet. Hon har egenskaper likt en sagoprinsessas moral och dygder. B&ouml;ckerna har element av b&aring;de socialrealism och saga. Fungerar det? Och finns det n&aring;got att vara tveksam till?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"34","title":"Svensk fantasy idag","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"15:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0041","name":"Patrik Centerwall (moderator)"},{"id":"0014","name":"Amanda Landegren"},{"id":"A0057","name":"Stefan H\u00f6gberg"},{"id":"A0094","name":"Kristina H\u00e5rd"}],"desc":"<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #212529; font-family: apple-system, system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, 'Noto Sans', sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol', 'Noto Color Emoji'; font-size: 13.3333px;\">Det har skrivits fantasy i Sverige under l&aring;ng tid, men sedan b&ouml;rjan av 2000-talet har det kommit mer och mer. Vad skrivs i dag, hur har genren utvecklats, varf&ouml;r &auml;r det s&aring; m&aring;nga som vill skriva fantasy och finns det tillr&auml;ckligt med l&auml;sare. Kort sagt hur ser svensk fantasy ut i dag?<\/span><\/div>","links":[]},{"id":"35","title":"Strong Female Characters","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"20:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0017","name":"\u00c5sa Lundstr\u00f6m (moderator)"},{"id":"0027","name":"T. L. Huchu"},{"id":"0030","name":"Elin Holmerin"},{"id":"A0011","name":"Jukka Halme"},{"id":"A0018","name":"Cheryl Morgan"}],"desc":"<p>How have gender roles changed over time in SF and fantasy?&nbsp; Female characters take on ever-greater roles in fantastic fiction. Have strong female characters displaced male ones? Is it because women play an ever-larger role in society generally? Do female characters play a more significant role in science fiction and fantasy because more women are writing and creating fantastic worlds? How do changing gender dynamics affect how one reads, or how viewers appreciate what they watch?<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"36","title":"The dark forest in Fantasyland","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"21:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0033","name":"Marianna \"Kisu\" Leikomaa (moderator)"},{"id":"0012","name":"Oskar K\u00e4llner"},{"id":"A0094","name":"Kristina H\u00e5rd"},{"id":"A0110","name":"Juliet McKenna"},{"id":"A0115","name":"Thomas Olivieri"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The forest has always been a important part of fantasy, fairy tales and horror. The Nordic countries are covered by forest. Is the forest perceived, described and used in a different way in the Nordic countries compared with stories from other parts of the world?<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-bae99ce6-7fff-1f82-a578-38d1a28bd294\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"38","title":"F\u00f6rfattarfika: Lena Karlin och \u00c5sa Schwarz","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Meeting"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"13:00","mins":"45","loc":["Annat - -"],"people":[{"id":"0005","name":"Lena Karlin (moderator)"},{"id":"0008","name":"\u00c5sa Schwarz"}],"desc":"<p>M&ouml;t Lena och &Aring;sa i ett informellt samtal.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"39","title":"Fika with Juliet McKenna","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Meeting"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"15:00","mins":"45","loc":["Annat - -"],"people":[{"id":"A0110","name":"Juliet McKenna"}],"desc":"<p>Meet Juliet for an informal small group conversation.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"40","title":"Fika with T L Huchu","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Projected Media"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"13:00","mins":"45","loc":["Annat - -"],"people":[{"id":"0027","name":"T. L. Huchu"}],"desc":"<p>Meet Tendai for an informal small group conversation.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"41","title":"Att skriva science fiction och fantasy ","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"10:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0053","name":"Sten Rosendahl (moderator)"},{"id":"A0045","name":"Nashwan Ghazy"},{"id":"A0106","name":"Boel Bermann"},{"id":"A0116","name":"J\u00f6rgen Hassler"},{"id":"A0135","name":"Camilla Linde"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Vill du skriva sf och fantasy utan <\/span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">att fastna p&aring; v&auml;rldsbygge eller enstaka karakt&auml;rer? <\/span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">D&aring; &auml;r den h&auml;r diskussionen n&aring;got f&ouml;r dig! Panelen diskuterar hur man skriver fantastik med fokus p&aring; att skapa en tilltalande ber&auml;ttelse.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-25b181d8-7fff-fe02-2f7e-d296cabc9d3f\"><\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"43","title":"\u00c5ke Ohlmarks, Tolkien och s\u00e4llskapen ","tags":["Track:Fan Interest","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"12:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0041","name":"Patrik Centerwall (moderator)"},{"id":"0031","name":"M\u00e4rta Myrstener"},{"id":"A0009","name":"John-Henri Holmberg"},{"id":"A0150","name":"Anders Stenstr\u00f6m"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&Aring;ke Ohlmarks &ouml;vers&auml;ttning av Sagan om ringen &auml;r mycket omdiskuterad. Det var inte bara &ouml;vers&auml;ttningen som diskuterades. Hur gick det till n&auml;r &Aring;ke Ohlmarks gick fr&aring;n att ha varit v&auml;nligt inst&auml;lld till Tolkiens&auml;llskapen i Sverige till att anklaga s&auml;llskapen f&ouml;r satanism? Varf&ouml;r skrev han \"Tolkien och den svarta magin\"?<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-6f36971b-7fff-87bd-a196-4051ef5fc379\"><\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"44","title":"Rymdoperan, den nya rymdoperan \u2013 och rymdoperan i dag","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"20:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0009","name":"John-Henri Holmberg (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">F&ouml;rst kom rymdoperan, enkla men popul&auml;ra &auml;ventyrshistorier om <\/span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">drabbningar i fj&auml;rran rymder. P&aring; 1970- och 1980-talet &aring;teruppstod<\/span><br style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" \/><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">rymdoperan, nu enligt m&aring;nga tillskyndare mer inriktad p&aring; <\/span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">personutveckling, en mer litter&auml;r form och utforskning av moraliska och<\/span><br style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" \/><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">sociala fr&aring;gor. St&auml;mmer det syns&auml;ttet? Vilka &auml;r de mest representativa, <\/span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">intressanta och b&auml;sta exemplen p&aring; de olika periodernas rymdoperor? Och <\/span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">hur b&ouml;r den som skrivs i dag karakt&auml;riseras?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"47","title":"Old gods in new times","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"11:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0018","name":"Rolf Andersen (moderator)"},{"id":"0027","name":"T. L. Huchu"},{"id":"A0042","name":"Gunilla Rydbeck"},{"id":"A0110","name":"Juliet McKenna"},{"id":"A0188","name":"Dhruv Phadke"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">It is not easy to be a god or a supernatural being in our time. There are many examples of how old gods and other beings try to survive in the modern world. How does fantasy deal with these ideas? Examples include Shigidi, American Gods, The Green Man's Heir, and Rivers of London.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-febeeab7-7fff-c5f0-6374-0fe6c57ebfc6\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"48","title":"Sabriel - an underrated fantasy classic","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"14:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"0026","name":"Nina Tadsen (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Garth Nix's young adult novel \"Sabriel\" is an often overlooked gem in the conversation of children's fantasy classics. In this discussion group, we will delve into why this book is deserving of more recognition and exploration, exploring magic system, world-building, and characters as well as how it contributes to the broader landscape of fantasy fiction. If you haven't read this book, we hope we can convince you to give it a try! <\/span><\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"49","title":"50 years of The Dispossessed","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"16:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0018","name":"Cheryl Morgan (moderator)"},{"id":"A0019","name":"Saga Bolund"},{"id":"A0126","name":"Markku Soikkeli"},{"id":"A0157","name":"Jerry M\u00e4\u00e4tt\u00e4"},{"id":"A0176","name":"Joachim Bj\u00f6rk"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-9396a3bb-7fff-a704-e0ba-559270531dfe\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">2024 marks the 50 year anniversary of Ursula K. Le Guin's classic science fiction novel The Dispossessed. One of the few books to win the Hugo, Locus and Nebula Awards, it is widely considered a defining work of SFF literature. What made the book so beloved and what keeps people reading it to this day? Does it read as a political manifesto, a character study, a speculative thought experiment - or all of the above? What themes resonated with contemporary audiences, and what can we take from the novel when rereading it 50 years on? <\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"51","title":"Svenska kongresser p\u00e5 70- och 80-talet","tags":["Track:Fan Interest","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"16:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0136","name":"Ylva Sp\u00e5ngberg (moderator)"},{"id":"0005","name":"Lena Karlin"},{"id":"A0014","name":"John-Henri Holmberg"},{"id":"A0039","name":"Birgitta Stridh"},{"id":"A0197","name":"Kaj Harju"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-7a434be1-7fff-0004-0812-3e389f3f8f54\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">H&ouml;r ber&auml;ttelserna av de som var med. Bildbevis kommer att presenteras.<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"52","title":"Gudar och v\u00e4sen i svenskspr\u00e5kig fantasy","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"19:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0041","name":"Patrik Centerwall (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-2c0787fa-7fff-8284-760e-71776c6b4521\"><\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: #ffffff; margin-bottom: 0cm;\">Hur mycket har fornnordisk mytologi och nordisk folktro inspirerat den svenskspr&aring;kiga fantasyllitteraturen? Hur mycket letar sig gudar och v&auml;sen in i ber&auml;ttelserna, vad f&aring;r de d&aring; f&ouml;r roll och hur f&ouml;rh&aring;ller sig litteraturen till gamla tiders myter, sagor och legender?<\/p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-color: #ffffff; margin-bottom: 0cm;\">Det h&auml;r f&ouml;redraget belyser hur gudar och v&auml;sen anv&auml;nds av svenskspr&aring;kiga fantasyf&ouml;rfattare, och bjuder naturligtvis ocks&aring; p&aring; en del boktips.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"54","title":"A conversation about urban fantasy for young readers ","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"17:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0014","name":"Amanda Landegren"},{"id":"A0062","name":"Stefan Ekman"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14.6667px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Amanda Landegren and Stefan Ekman discuss the themes and tropes that characterise children&rsquo;s and young adult urban fantasy. What does the genre look like? How is it different from &rdquo;adult&rdquo; urban fantasy? The genre&rsquo;s development is also put in a historical context, where prominent and influential works are highlighted.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"55","title":"AI-prompta ett fantastikomslag","tags":["Track:Art","Division:Programming","Type:Participatory Event"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"15:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"0022","name":"J\u00f6rgen J\u00f6r\u00e4lv"}],"desc":"<p>Kom med f&ouml;rslag och id&eacute;er och skapa ett fantastikomslag tillsammans med J&ouml;rgen J&ouml;r&auml;lv. Han anv&auml;nder dagligen AI i sitt arbete som grafisk formgivare och kommer att ber&auml;tta om n&aring;gra anv&auml;ndbara tj&auml;nster och tips.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"56","title":"It\u2019s Not Clich\u00e9d, It\u2019s Iterating","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"21:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0057","name":"Stefan H\u00f6gberg"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333px; background-color: #ffffff;\">'Inventive fantasy' sometimes seems like a contradiction in terms. Do we really need more fairies and magical swords? Yes, says doctor Matthew Sangster in his latest book. Fantasy iterates, explores variations on common themes, and that is how literature used to work. Others want originality, and there certainly is inventive fantasy&hellip; or is there? What do we even mean by originality? Stefan H&ouml;gberg investigates.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"57","title":"What Twelve Years of Research Taught Me about Urban Fantasy","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"13:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0062","name":"Stefan Ekman"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">In 2012, Stefan Ekman first wondered what social criticism had to do with urban fantasy. Now, he can finally provide a concise summary of his recently completed research project on the subject. The presentation will discuss some insights into the characteristics and history of the urban fantasy genre, such as thoughts about why cities are not obligatory urban fantasy settings, how the genre&rsquo;s historical development resembles a bundle of threads, and what modernity has to do with any of this. (For those interested, his book on the subject is available for free download at&nbsp;<\/span><a style=\"color: #1155cc; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.3998\/mpub.14414299\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/doi.org\/10.3998\/mpub.14414299&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1726220346865000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1b9RPr57lVNI1pIxln7esT\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.3998\/mpub.<wbr \/>14414299<\/a><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">.)<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"59","title":"Turf - an introduction","tags":["Track:Gaming","Division:Gaming","Type:Workshop"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"13:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0039","name":"Birgitta Stridh (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p>Turf is a kind of orienteering that uses the GPS techology on a smartphone and was started 2010. Get information about the game, how to play and some exercise, meeting new people. You will never be lost when playing Turf.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"62","title":"\"Herding cats\" - how to moderate a panel","tags":["Track:Fan Interest","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"13:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0004","name":"Timothy Johansson (moderator)"},{"id":"A0003","name":"Britt-Louise Viklund"},{"id":"A0011","name":"Jukka Halme"},{"id":"A0018","name":"Cheryl Morgan"},{"id":"A0097","name":"Johan Anglemark"}],"desc":"<p>The success of a panel naturally depends on the subject and the participants, but the moderators impact could be crucial as well. But how do you prepare to moderate a panel? How do you handle a discussion that has steered away from the subject or if one panelist is about to take over the conversation? When should you let the audience in and how do you interrupt an audience question that just goes on forever? This and much more will be discussed in this panel of experienced moderators.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"63","title":"Sentient spaceships","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"10:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0017","name":"Ian Sales (moderator)"},{"id":"0023","name":"Tommy Persson "},{"id":"A0132","name":"Michael Petersen"},{"id":"A0138","name":"Saara Henriksson"},{"id":"A0151","name":"H\u00e5kan Wester"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Living and intelligent spaceships are common in science fiction literature, in film, and on television. How is this idea used in different stories? Which ones do we like best, and why? Is the idea of contact with a living spaceship a kind of wish fulfillment to be compared to fantasy's contact with a powerful dragon?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"64","title":"Hur l\u00e4ser man klassisk sf idag?","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"12:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0097","name":"Johan Anglemark (moderator)"},{"id":"0011","name":"Anna Davour"},{"id":"0028","name":"Anders Hedenlund"},{"id":"A0014","name":"John-Henri Holmberg"},{"id":"A0140","name":"Gabriella Gomez"}],"desc":"<p>F&ouml;rfattare som Asimov, Clarke, Heinlein och andra har format den genre vi l&auml;ser i dag. Men vissa ber&auml;ttelser kan ha &aring;ldrats p&aring; ett s&auml;tt som g&ouml;r att de uppfattas som problematiska eller till och med oacceptabla av dagens l&auml;sare. Vilka och varf&ouml;r? Denna diskussion kommer att fundera kring hur en modern l&auml;sare kan hantera s&aring;dana ber&auml;ttelser.&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">Finns det verk och upphovspersoner som helt enkelt&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">inte kan accepteras idag, eller kan vi kanske l&auml;ra oss n&aring;got ocks&aring; av <\/span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">verk skrivna med helt andra utg&aring;ngspunkter &auml;n dagens?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"65","title":"Encounters with aliens","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"14:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0029","name":"Janne (moderator)"},{"id":"0013","name":"Theodor Pipping"},{"id":"0018","name":"Rolf Andersen"},{"id":"0020","name":"Jenny Bristle"},{"id":"A0083","name":"Vesa Sis\u00e4tt\u00f6"}],"desc":"<p>Encounters with aliens have long been a common ingredient in science fiction stories. But do these depictions really say anything about us humans? One story becomes a cautionary reflection of Western colonization while another depicts a hope for the future. Are the dark and negative depictions simply just fear of change? What are the best, most interesting, and most credible descriptions of such encounters?&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"66","title":"Guilty pleasures in sff","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"19:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"0024","name":"Gwen Frazer (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Sometimes it's not the \"finest\" works that are the most fun. Which works in literature, film and television are you a bit embarrassed to admit that you like? What makes you feel ashamed about them? Come and share your shameful favorites.<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"67","title":"Comfort reading","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"12:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"0004","name":"Timothy Johansson (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">There are books that you read time after time. They may not be the best works, but they are still the ones you pick from the bookshelf when you are sad, tired or need to de-stress. Which books do you return to and why? Is there anything that unites such books?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"69","title":"Modern svensk f\u00e4ktnings utveckling 1900-2024","tags":["Track:Theme","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"11:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0008","name":"Carolina G\u00f3mez Lagerl\u00f6f (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p>En genomg&aring;ng av svensk f&auml;ktnings utveckling fr&aring;n 1900-talets b&ouml;rjan tills nu. Carolina, som b&ouml;rjade f&auml;kta 1976, ber&auml;ttar om hur f&auml;ktningen utvecklats med ett visst fokus p&aring; damf&auml;ktning.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"71","title":"Fanfondsauktion","tags":["Track:Fan Interest","Division:Programming","Type:Participatory Event"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"19:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0105","name":"Fia Karlsson"}],"desc":"<p>Auktion till st&ouml;d f&ouml;r fanfonderna TAFF, EFF och GUFF! K&ouml;p intressanta saker och g&ouml;r en god g&auml;rning.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"75","title":"Unforgettable characters ","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Discussion Group"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"21:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"0004","name":"Timothy Johansson (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Some literary characters are more memorable and loved, or hated, than others. Think of Sherlock Holmes, Dracula or Frankenstein's monster that keeps coming back in new interpretations. What makes a character memorable over time? Is a \"villain\" more memorable and loved than a hero, and if so, why? What modern examples are there of memorable characters that will live on in the future?<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"78","title":"Femmes fatales and Dark Lords - Gender in Speculative Villains","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"21:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0013","name":"Artemis Kelosaari"},{"id":"A0017","name":"\u00c5sa Lundstr\u00f6m"},{"id":"A0174","name":"Tina Skupin"}],"desc":"<p>Ambition and manipulation are often defining characteristics of villains, but how do gendered expectations influence the portrayal of male and female antagonists? This panel explores the gendered aspects of villainy in fantasy and science fiction, from subtle psychological warfare to brute strength.<\/p>\r\n<p>How do societal ideas of femininity and masculinity shape the way these characters wield power and command fear?<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"82","title":"Behind the scenes at Worldcon","tags":["Track:Fan Interest","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"15:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0049","name":"Shana Worthen (moderator)"},{"id":"A0008","name":"Carolina G\u00f3mez Lagerl\u00f6f"},{"id":"A0020","name":"Ann Olsson Rousset"},{"id":"A0029","name":"Janne"}],"desc":"<p>Many of us attended this year's World Science Fiction Convention (Worldcon) in Glasgow in August. Some of us were amongst the hundreds of volunteers who brought the convention to Glasgow in the first place.<\/p>\r\n<p>Find out what happens behind the scenes at a Worldcon, focusing particularly on this year's in Glasgow. What is it like to spend months or years helping to bring a Worldcon to reality? How do WSFS rules affect what a Worldcon can and cannot do? How does city affect what kind of a Worldcon the convention is? How did this year's go, at least, according to our panellists?<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"84","title":"AI and self-awareness","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"12:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0046","name":"Linn Liljemo (moderator)"},{"id":"0008","name":"\u00c5sa Schwarz"},{"id":"A0054","name":"Bj\u00f8rn Tore Sund"},{"id":"A0106","name":"Boel Bermann"},{"id":"A0154","name":"Larissa Ekonoja"}],"desc":"<p>Is there a real risk of AI becoming self-aware? If so, should we accept that they have as much free will as we humans, and teach them ethics and the difference between right and wrong? Will we get partners or servants? Will the use of AI in warfare make it impossible to bring someone to justice? The panel discusses these issues and gives examples from sf.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"85","title":"Brave New Plate - Science and the future of food.","tags":["Track:Science","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"11:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0010","name":"Torill Kornfeldt (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Science journalist Torill Kornfeldt delves deep into the research on the future of food. Will it be all about insect burgers, algae smoothies, and nutrition pills, or are there other visions of what, how, and why we will eat in the future?<\/span><\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"86","title":"Frivoliteter- prova p\u00e5","tags":["Track:Maker","Division:Programming","Type:Workshop"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"10:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0020","name":"Ann Olsson Rousset (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p>Frivoliteter &auml;r ett hantverk d&auml;r man med g&ouml;r spets med knutar. Prova p&aring;!<\/p>\r\n<p>Programpunkten &auml;r begr&auml;nsad till &aring;tta (8) deltagare. Deltagarlista kommer att finnas i registreringen.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"88","title":"Ur led \u00e4r tiden","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"14:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0146","name":"Anders Blixt (moderator)"},{"id":"0005","name":"Lena Karlin"},{"id":"0008","name":"\u00c5sa Schwarz"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">Tiden har alltid varit ett centralt tema inom SF. Vad skulle h&auml;nda om tiden kunde manipuleras f&ouml;r olika syften? Vilka problem skulle uppst&aring;? Deltagarna funderar om tiden och ber&auml;ttelser som tar upp tiden fr&aring;n olika perspektiv.<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"91","title":"Haunting the Narrative - The Role of Ghosts in Speculative fiction","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"18:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0027","name":"T. L. Huchu"},{"id":"A0013","name":"Artemis Kelosaari"},{"id":"A0134","name":"Lisa Ylitalo"},{"id":"A0174","name":"Tina Skupin"}],"desc":"<p>Ghosts have long been central figures in speculative fiction, in everything from gothic horror to urban fantasy. This panel explores the symbolic and narrative power of ghosts - what do they tell us about fear, memory, trauma, and unresolved histories? What role do they play in world-building, character development, and the exploration of life and death? What keeps these apparitions haunting characters and readers alike?&nbsp; &nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"92","title":"Christopher Polhem och SF","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"17:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0029","name":"Ahrvid Engholm"}],"desc":"<p>Vetenskapsmannen Christopher Polhem (1661-1751) var geniet som effektiviserade Falu koppargruva, skapade ett \"mekaniskt alfabete\", grundade Laboratorium Mechanicum som senare blev KTH - och var den f&ouml;rste sf-f&ouml;rfattaren p&aring; svenska! 1710 nedtecknade han \"Nyheter fr&aring;n M&aring;nen\" d&auml;r en same skickades ut i rymden och bland annat studerade m&aring;nbornas spr&aring;k. Undrar du vad \"Spavilafk ikav sve\" betyder f&aring;r du h&auml;r svaret...<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"93","title":"The State of Publishing: A Conversation","tags":["Track:GOH","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"15:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0018","name":"Cheryl Morgan (moderator)"},{"id":"A0110","name":"Juliet McKenna"}],"desc":"<p>Juliet McKenna and Cheryl Morgan discuss the state of publishing today. This wide-ranging exploration will be between an author and her publisher, between a defender of authors against unjust legislation and a champion of translation and intercultural dialogue. It is likely to cover anything from copyright protections to e-books, publishing corporations to self-publishing, editing to translation.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"94","title":"Some Notes on Barad-d\u00fbr","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"11:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0150","name":"Anders Stenstr\u00f6m (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">Beregond takes a look at <\/span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">what Tolkien told us about Sauron's abode<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"95","title":"Stockholm's Invisible Bridges","tags":["Track:Theme","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"14:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0049","name":"Shana Worthen (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p>Stockholm, city of bridges, Venice of the North: past advertising campaigns for the city have highlighted its visible bridges. This talk will highlight lesser-seen bridges, whether because they are small, obscure, no longer there, or just entirely invisible these days. With plenty of illustrations of where the bridges might be, since this presentation by a historian of technology was born out of an Instagram photography project.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"96","title":"Skr\u00e4ck i vardag och familj","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"16:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0133","name":"Gunilla Jonsson (moderator)"},{"id":"A0056","name":"Sara Engstr\u00f6m"},{"id":"A0132","name":"Michael Petersen"},{"id":"A0134","name":"Lisa Ylitalo"},{"id":"A0135","name":"Camilla Linde"}],"desc":"<p>Skr&auml;ck i litteratur f&aring;r inte vara alltf&ouml;r osannolik f&ouml;r att ha effekt. B&auml;st blir det om l&auml;saren k&auml;nner igen sig i milj&ouml; och &auml;r trygg med sina n&auml;rmaste. Panelen diskuterar hur detta g&ouml;rs b&auml;st och tar upp exempel.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"99","title":"K\u00f6ren Patacar","tags":["Track:Music","Division:Programming","Type:Participatory Event"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"16:00","mins":"30","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":null,"desc":"<p>K&ouml;ren Patacar med deltagare fr&aring;n Tolkiens&auml;llskapet Forodrim sjunger.<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"100","title":"Varf\u00f6r ska astronomer leta efter utomjordingar","tags":["Track:Science","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"10:00","mins":"45","loc":["Stora scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0011","name":"Anna Davour (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">F&ouml;r 60 &aring;r sedan gjorde Frank Drake det f&ouml;rsta moderna f&ouml;rs&ouml;ket att<\/span><br style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" \/><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">spana efter utomjordiska civilisationer med sitt Project Ozma.<\/span><br style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" \/><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">Fortfarande har ingen hittat n&aring;gra tydliga tecken p&aring; att n&aring;gon annan<\/span><br style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" \/><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">finns d&auml;r ute. Astronomer kommer hela tiden p&aring; nya s&auml;tt att s&ouml;ka<\/span><br style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" \/><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">vidare. Vad &auml;r po&auml;ngen med det, och hur g&aring;r de till v&auml;ga? Vi kikar p&aring;<\/span><br style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" \/><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\">n&aring;gra av de senaste id&eacute;erna och en eller annan kontrovers.<\/span><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"102","title":"Blixt-Grodon - Hj\u00e4ltarnas Hj\u00e4lte!","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Single Speaker\/Lecture"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"11:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"0022","name":"J\u00f6rgen J\u00f6r\u00e4lv (moderator)"}],"desc":"<p><!--StartFragment--><span data-olk-copy-source=\"MessageBody\">Blixt-Grodon, de existentiella fr&aring;gornas och de kniviga situationernas m&auml;stare fyller 60 &aring;r. Serien Blixt-Grodon publicerades i Stockholms Universitets studentk&aring;rs tidskrift Gaudeamus 1964-1988. Den har sedan dess &aring;terpublicerats i bland annat DN och Jules Verne-magasinet samt i samlingsutg&aring;vor 1968, 2002 och nu i &aring;r samlades den kompletta produktionen i bokform. Skaparen Lars &rdquo;Lon&rdquo; Olsson &auml;r en av de flitigaste fanzineillustrat&ouml;rerna genom &aring;ren och f&ouml;redraget bjuder p&aring; en bildkavalkad ur Lons digra produktion.&nbsp;<\/span><!--EndFragment--><\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"106","title":"Fr\u00e5n litteratur till dataspel","tags":["Track:Gaming","Division:Programming","Type:Panel"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"20:00","mins":"45","loc":["Lilla scen - 1"],"people":[{"id":"A0094","name":"Kristina H\u00e5rd (moderator)"},{"id":"0012","name":"Oskar K\u00e4llner"},{"id":"A0173","name":"Thomas \u00c5rnfelt"}],"desc":"<p>Det finns m&aring;nga exempel p&aring; kopplingar mellan fantastiken som litteraturform och som dataspel, inte minst i svensk fandom. Panelen kommer att diskutera dessa kopplingar och skillnaden mellan fantastik i litter&auml;r form och som dataspel, liksom hur det g&aring;r till att transformera litteratur till dataspel. Vilka f&ouml;rdelar och nackdelar finns med de olika uttryckss&auml;tten?<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"110","title":"\u00d6ppet spel","tags":["Track:Gaming","Division:Programming","Type:Open Gaming"],"date":"2024-11-01","time":"18:00","mins":"180","loc":["Spelrummet - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0024","name":"Martin Rundkvist"}],"desc":"<p>Vill du spela spel? Martin Rundkvist &auml;r v&auml;rd f&ouml;r spelrummet och vill g&auml;rna spela!<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"111","title":"\u00d6ppet spel","tags":["Track:Gaming","Division:Programming","Type:Open Gaming"],"date":"2024-11-02","time":"13:00","mins":"180","loc":["Spelrummet - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0024","name":"Martin Rundkvist"}],"desc":"<p>Vill du spela spel? Martin Rundkvist &auml;r v&auml;rd f&ouml;r spelrummet och vill g&auml;rna spela!<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"112","title":"\u00d6ppet spel","tags":["Track:Gaming","Division:Programming","Type:Open Gaming"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"12:00","mins":"120","loc":["Spelrummet - 2"],"people":[{"id":"A0024","name":"Martin Rundkvist"}],"desc":"<p>Vill du spela spel? Martin Rundkvist &auml;r v&auml;rd f&ouml;r spelrummet och han vill g&auml;rna spela!<\/p>","links":[]},{"id":"113","title":"H\u00f6gl\u00e4sning \/ Reading","tags":["Track:Literature","Division:Programming","Type:Reading"],"date":"2024-11-03","time":"12:00","mins":"45","loc":["Luigi - 2"],"people":null,"desc":"<p>F&ouml;rfattare l&auml;ser ur sina verk. Authors read from their work.<\/p>","links":[]}]